          <p>To submit statements, you must create an account. You agree to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide accurate and complete information during registration</li>
            <li>Maintain the security of your password and account</li>
            <li>Accept responsibility for all activities that occur under your account</li>
            <li>Notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.1 Account Security</h3>
          <p>
            You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials. SpeechKarma will not be
            liable for any loss or damage arising from your failure to protect your account information.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. User-Generated Content</h2>
          <p>
            SpeechKarma allows authenticated users to submit statements made by politicians. By submitting content, you:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Affirm that the statement is a genuine public statement made by the attributed politician</li>
            <li>
              Grant SpeechKarma a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to display your submitted content
            </li>
            <li>Retain ownership of the content you submit</li>
            <li>Accept that submitted statements become part of the public record on our platform</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.1 Grace Period</h3>
          <p>
            You may edit or delete your submitted statements within 15 minutes of creation. After this grace period,
            statements become permanent public records and cannot be modified or removed by users.
          </p>

          <h3>3.2 Content Standards</h3>
          <p>All submitted statements must:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Be factual representations of statements actually made by the attributed politician</li>
            <li>Include accurate date and time information</li>
            <li>Not contain spam, malicious code, or inappropriate content</li>
            <li>Comply with applicable laws and regulations</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Submit false or misleading statements</li>
            <li>Attribute statements to politicians who did not make them</li>
